    <note type="source of activity">"Philteas, of Calacte, an historical writer, the author of a work
      in the Ionic dialect, entitled Ναξιακά, of which the third book is quoted by Tzetzes (Schol. ad Lycophr. 633).
      He is also mentioned in a passage of Eustathius (ad Hom. p. 1885. 51), where, however, the name is corrupted 
      into Philetas, and Eudocia, copying the error, places the Ναξλακά among the works of Philetas of Cos (Violar. p. 424)..."</note>
